<Layout
	title="CDCP Dentist in Surrey, BC"
	description="Canary Dental is a proud provider for the Canadian Dental Care Plan (CDCP). Learn how to use your benefits for cleanings, fillings, and more at our Surrey clinic."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-04-29')}
	heroImage={HeroImage}
>
	<h2>Your Trusted CDCP Provider in Surrey</h2>
	<p>
		The <strong>Canadian Dental Care Plan (CDCP)</strong> is a fantastic government initiative designed to lower dental costs for eligible Canadians. At Canary Dental Clinic, we are proud to be an officially registered CDCP provider, ensuring that our community receives the high-quality care they deserve without the financial stress.
	</p>

	<h3>What Services Are Covered Under CDCP?</h3>
	<p>
		The CDCP covers a wide range of essential dental services. Depending on your eligibility, the plan may cover:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Preventative Care:</strong> Exams, X-rays, and <a href="/dental-cleaning">professional dental cleanings</a>.</li>
		<li><strong>Restorative Services:</strong> Dental fillings to treat cavities.</li>
		<li><strong>Oral Surgery:</strong> Tooth extractions, including <a href="/wisdom-tooth-extraction">wisdom tooth removal</a>.</li>
		<li><strong>Endodontics:</strong> Root canal treatments for infected teeth.</li>
		<li><strong>Periodontics:</strong> Deep scaling for gum disease.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>How to Use Your CDCP Benefits at Canary Dental</h3>
	<ol>
		<li><strong>Step 1: Check Eligibility.</strong> Ensure you have received your welcome letter and Sun Life CDCP card.</li>
		<li><strong>Step 2: Book Your Appointment.</strong> Contact our clinic. Let us know you are a CDCP patient.</li>
		<li><strong>Step 3: Bring Your Documents.</strong> Bring your Sun Life CDCP card and a valid piece of ID to your appointment.</li>
		<li><strong>Step 4: Receive Care.</strong> We will bill Sun Life directly. You are only responsible for your specific co-payment (if applicable).</li>
	</ol>

	<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
	<details>
		<summary>Is everything 100% free with the CDCP?</summary>
		<p>Not necessarily. Depending on your adjusted family net income, you may have a co-payment (e.g., 40%, 50%, or 60%). Additionally, if a specific treatment costs more than the CDCP established fees, patients may need to pay the difference. Our staff will always explain any out-of-pocket costs before beginning treatment.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>Do I still need my private employer insurance?</summary>
		<p>If you have private insurance through your employer, you must use it as your primary coverage. The CDCP is designed to help those without access to private insurance. For a detailed comparison, read our guide on <a href="/blog/cdcp-vs-private-insurance-surrey">CDCP vs Private Dental Insurance</a>.</p>
	</details>

	<h3>Ready to Book?</h3>
	<p>
		Don't let your oral health wait. If your CDCP coverage has begun, contact our fluent <a href="/mandarin-speaking-dentist">English and Mandarin speaking team</a> to schedule your visit.
	</p>
	<p style="text-align:center;">
		<a href="https://line.me/ti/p/4RpjC2r6Hq" style="display:inline-block; background:var(--accent); color:white; padding:1em 2em; border-radius:8px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:bold; font-size:1.1em;">Book Your CDCP Appointment</a>
	</p>
</Layout>
